reviews.text: If you are looking for traditional dim sum. I wouldn’t recommend this place. It’s more fusion and creative dim sum, which has its charm but may not be my cup of tea. The interior design is really nice. Probably a good place to have dinner with colleagues.

We just had dessert here and the food was excellent (the pineapple puff birds are adorable and the specialty buns are too cute). Highly recommend for some great pics! HOWEVER. The service was really bad. They forgot our drinks and the waiters kept ignoring us for about 45 minutes. Much of the wait staff was also very rude. Most alarming was seeing the manager (I think he was the manager, he was wearing a button down instead of the t-shirt everyone else on) PUNCH a waiter THREE TIMES in the face for some reason. This was out in the open in front of the whole restaurant (though it would be unacceptable anywhere). That was honestly insane...

Great food but confused service!

This place is for the gram! The food presentation is great and everything was quite tasty. The majority of our dishes were well done but we did over order, unbeknown to us at the time.

Admittedly the waitress serving us had a trainee tag on, but there were two things missing in the service which was irritating.

1. She didn’t greet or speak at all. She was quiet as a mouse to the point where when we asked her something she walked off on us without acknowledging whether she understood what we wanted. 

2. She knew the table size and as the menu doesn’t show pics of what a quantity looks like. She should have guided us on what and how much to order.
What’s not to like about this fun restaurant? It’s cute AND tasty. Look at this poor little red bean bun... aaaahh!

Fun ambiance. Adorable dim sum but the food itself is under par. Quite mediocre. But you go there for the creativity in the food design and less for the taste. Great place to bring out of Townes visiting Hong Kong. Conveniently located in central, a hop skip and jump away from many hotels in the area and IFC mall.
